collection.description:
What started out as doodles left on restaurant and bar receipts in 2015 is now a collection of 10,000 unique programmatically generated NFTs on the Ethereum blockchain. Based on the art of Arlo Eisenberg, Drug Receipts is founded on the principles of art, science, skepticism, subversion, and community.

Led by four main characters, Cap, Tabbi, Rex, and Syrin, Drug Receipts is at once irresistibly cute and also brazenly provocative. Drug Receipts does not take a position on whether drugs are good or bad. All of the characters are deliberately ambiguous—Illicit substances that can be used for healing or recreation. Responsibly or recklessly.

Drug Receipts is a defense of nuance. It is a prescription against polarization. Become a pusher of deeper and more thoughtful content. Trade in illicit conversations. Join the growing legion of Drug Snugglers and help spread Drug Receipts’ unique brand of mind-altering substance.
collection.name: Drug Receipts Collection

asset_contract.name: Non Visible Art
asset_contract.description:
The Non-Visible Art is a collection of 777 authentic pieces. Each piece is different because you may see something different on it!

Some may create their best piece of art while looking at one of the Non-Visible Art pieces.

Some may talk about how crazy it is that something like this can be so much valuable.

This art is too special to be owned by everyone. That's why we are listing it on the blockchain.

"Non-Visible" means something that can't be seen at the time, possibly due to ones line of sight. "Invisible" means, the object is not visible by nature. As this art is made for everyone to imagine, and it can be perceived differently, it is more accurate to call it "Non-Visible".

We hope, it will motivate and will inspire people to think more open-mindedly and to be even more creative even more.

Did you came up with some amazing idea, while looking at Non-Visible Art?

Make sure to share it and write about it! Tag us @NonVisibleNFT on Twitter!

assets.description:
The Sozoro Collection is an art project by artist Takayuki Yokoyama.

Sozoro is a Japanese term that describes the emotions we experience without reason. The same kanji in sozoro is also in the word for manga,the popular Japanese art form. Manga literally translates to “whimsical pictures”-an apt description of Hokusai Katsushika’s collection of sketches“Hokusai Manga”

This Collection is about continually creating work in the limited peaceful time available. It is not bound by any ideology or message. Instead,He created these pieces in a manner that can be described as sozoro; out of all the things he had seen or imagined, he simply depicted whatever he felt like depicting.

All works are limited to a maximum of 5 per theme. Each piece includes a serial number & signature. A special feature of this NST is that only buyers will be provided with a DL link to Hi-resolution data for 16:9(3840x2160px)digital display.

What started out as doodles left on restaurant and bar receipts in 2015 is now a collection of 10,000 unique programmatically generated NFTs on the Ethereum blockchain. Based on the art of Arlo Eisenberg, Drug Receipts is founded on the principles of art, science, skepticism, subversion, and community.

Led by four main characters, Cap, Tabbi, Rex, and Syrin, Drug Receipts is at once irresistibly cute and also brazenly provocative. Drug Receipts does not take a position on whether drugs are good or bad. All of the characters are deliberately ambiguous—Illicit substances that can be used for healing or recreation. collection.description:
What started out as doodles left on restaurant and bar receipts in 2015 is now a collection of 10,000 unique programmatically generated NFTs on the Ethereum blockchain. Based on the art of Arlo Eisenberg, Drug Receipts is founded on the principles of art, science, skepticism, subversion, and community.

Led by four main characters, Cap, Tabbi, Rex, and Syrin, Drug Receipts is at once irresistibly cute and also brazenly provocative. Drug Receipts does not take a position on whether drugs are good or bad. All of the characters are deliberately ambiguous—Illicit substances that can be used for healing or recreation. Responsibly or recklessly.

Drug Receipts is a defense of nuance. It is a prescription against polarization. Become a pusher of deeper and more thoughtful content. Trade in illicit conversations. Join the growing legion of Drug Snugglers and help spread Drug Receipts’ unique brand of mind-altering substance.
collection.name: DrugReceipts NFT

February 24, 2022 Russia started a full scale war in Ukraine. As I'm writing this, all my friends and family are either hiding in basements or protecting my country.  

This unique collection was created by a group of artists in occupied Kyiv. People literally created these pieces of art while hiding underground and hearing air strike sirens. 

The people of Ukraine are showing tremendous braveness and readiness to protect our land. Everyone is participating - and you can, too. 

The purpose of this collection is to provide help for civilians during war. YOU CAN HELP!

The collection will be updated daily.

All the profits will be doubled by my team and sent directly to humanitarian organizations in Ukraine. Ukrainian people are in need for medicine, food, diapers and much more. 

Слава Україні!
collection.name: Ukraine - you can help!

collection.description:
Average Creatures is the first all-handmade sculpture/photography NFT PFP hybrid collection on the block(chain).

That's right, each piece was made by hand and photographed separately. Inspired by ‘80s art, media, and entertainment in all of its practical effects glory, Average Creatures pays homage to that now oh so distant time in history: our childhood.

Each Average Creature in this collection is the curated result of a combination of hundreds of elements and layers, which were photographed and composited together to form a unique piece. Mixing several art techniques to create a visual style that defies convention, this project explores traditional art forms that have yet to be used together in any other PFP project. From set design to sculpting, costuming to painting, each Average Creature has a vivid personality that truly redefines how we think of the word “average.”

asset_contract.name: NFF
asset_contract.description:
NFTs for freedom represents hope. Our NFTs serve as an access pass to a world of possibility, collaboration, education & giving.  We combine digital art, physical art, photography & poetry, all in one.  We are hard pressed to find another NFT project that has done so. With lofty ambitions we aim to deliver means & opportunity to those in need. Our NFTs will provide access to exclusive "virtual" & "in-person" events within the NFTs for Freedom ecosystem; providing our holders with access to a wide variety of resources.  

Our genesis mint compensates hundreds of artists spanning over 30 countries; from visual artists to photographers, from poets to musicians. NFTs for Freedom will provide both financial & creative liberty for as many people as possible. Our NFT holders are helping us make that dream come true and we are dedicated to helping our holders realize their dreams as well. That is our mission and that is why we are here.

assets.name: I'm a standing Billiken born in Japan.
assets.description:
This is a standing Billiken born in Japan.
Billiken is known as the god of happiness, but Kyoto spiritual artist Hiroshi Inaoka talked with a friend during the Great East Japan Earthquake.
The friend said, "It's not the case when you're sitting in this emergency, even though you're a god. Don't stand up." That's why Mr. Inaoka flashed and made it.
It's a standing Billiken.
More than 100 standing Billikens were donated for reconstruction, and I was lucky from the donations. Some say that the business is prosperous.
And since I was also a friend, I had my guardian deity give me a present.
That is Billiken in this photo. This is a standing Billiken with red legs and the image of Santa.
